  "texts": [
    "Training in this method ensures the most reliable identification of the tasks.",
    "Once a task-dependent subspace has been identified, it could be removed by subtracting it from the entire weight space (layer-by-layer).",
    "While this may be effective at removing the task of interest, it leads to performance loss when similar tasks are also evaluated, i.e.",
    "ones that occupy similar subspaces.",
    "Therefore, a method is required that maintains the mutual information between these two subspaces, only removing the information unique to the task of interest."
  ],
